## ðŸ“„ Environment Variables (.env)

This project uses a `.env` file to securely store sensitive configuration details. Below is a description of all the environment variables used in this project.

---

### ðŸ”Œ Server Configuration

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `PORT` | Port number on which the backend server will run. Default is `5000`. |

---

### ðŸŒ Database Configuration

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `MONGO_URI` | MongoDB connection URI for connecting to MongoDB Atlas. Contains username, password, and cluster information. |

---

### ðŸ—ºï¸ Google Maps API

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` | Google Maps API Key used for geolocation and maps-related features. |

---

### ðŸ” Authentication

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `JWT_SECRET_KEY` | Secret key used for generating and verifying JWT tokens for authentication. |

---

### â˜ï¸ Cloudinary (Media Uploads)

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` | Cloud name used for Cloudinary image uploads. |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_KEY` | API Key for accessing Cloudinary services. |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET` | Secret key for accessing Cloudinary securely. |
| `CLOUDINARY_URL` | Optional Cloudinary URL format for SDKs. |

---

### ðŸ“§ Email Service (Nodemailer)

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `EMAIL_USER` | Email address used to send mails (OTP, confirmation, etc). |
| `EMAIL_PASS` | App-specific password or email access token used by Nodemailer. |

---

### ðŸ“ž Twilio (SMS/OTP)

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio Account SID for sending OTPs/messages. |
| `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN` | Twilio Auth Token for authentication. |
| `TWILIO_AUTH_NUMBER` | Phone number provided by Twilio to send SMS. |

---

### ðŸŒ Frontend URL

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `FRONTEND_URL` | URL of the frontend application (used in CORS, email links, redirects, etc). |

---

### âš ï¸ Security Warning

> **Important:**  
> Never commit your `.env` file to source control (GitHub).  
> Always add `.env` to your `.gitignore` file to prevent accidental exposure of sensitive data.

